rComments: When writing tests/midterms the answer is not correct unless you say it exactly the way it is written in the textbook or the way he said it in class.  He doesn't realize that people don't all think or learn the same way.  In that way, he is not a fair marker.

Material was tough as hell, but he made it work.  Explains very clearly, great at discussions, and very funny.  Tough but fair grader and in the end I got better than I thought I was going to.  Great class, you learn a lot about theory and literature.
